    <!-- ==================== ROLES & PERMISSIONS ==================== -->
    <div class="help-topic" id="topic-roles">
      <h2><i class="bi bi-people"></i> Roles & Permissions</h2>
      <p class="topic-desc">TaskFlow has two organization types and five user roles. Each role determines what you can see and do throughout the application.</p>

      <h3>Organization Types</h3>
      <p><strong>CLIENT</strong> &mdash; The external client organization. They create tasks, track progress, and view reports on work being done by the local team.</p>
      <p><strong>LOCAL</strong> &mdash; The internal team that executes tasks, earns rewards, and manages day-to-day operations.</p>

      <h3>User Roles</h3>

      <h4><span class="help-role-badge admin">CLIENT_ADMIN</span> Client Administrator</h4>
      <p>Full control within the Client organization. Can create and assign tasks, set rewards, view all reports, and monitor team performance. Has access to the admin dashboard with complete analytics.</p>

      <h4><span class="help-role-badge manager">CLIENT_MANAGER</span> Client Manager</h4>
      <p>Can create and assign tasks, set rewards, and view team reports. Similar to Client Admin but cannot manage users or system settings.</p>

      <h4><span class="help-role-badge admin">LOCAL_ADMIN</span> Local Administrator</h4>
      <p>Full system administration. Can create and manage users, manage tasks, approve/reject leaves, mark rewards as paid, override attendance records, create database backups, and access all reports. This is the most powerful role.</p>

      <h4><span class="help-role-badge manager">LOCAL_MANAGER</span> Local Manager</h4>
      <p>Can manage the local team: create users (LOCAL_USER only), create/reassign tasks, approve leaves, and view reports. Cannot manage system settings, backups, or override attendance.</p>

      <h4><span class="help-role-badge user">LOCAL_USER</span> Local User</h4>
      <p>The individual team member. Can view assigned tasks, start sessions, complete tasks, create personal adhoc tasks, apply for leaves, use chat (reply only), and view their own progress and attendance.</p>

      <h3>Quick Reference Table</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Create tasks for others</strong> &mdash; Admin, Manager</li>
        <li><strong>Create personal adhoc tasks</strong> &mdash; All roles</li>
        <li><strong>Start new chats</strong> &mdash; Admin, Manager</li>
        <li><strong>Reply in chats</strong> &mdash; All roles</li>
        <li><strong>Approve/reject leaves</strong> &mdash; Admin, Manager</li>
        <li><strong>View team reports</strong> &mdash; Admin, Manager</li>
        <li><strong>Override attendance</strong> &mdash; Admin only</li>
        <li><strong>Mark rewards as paid</strong> &mdash; Admin only</li>
        <li><strong>Manage backups</strong> &mdash; Admin only</li>
        <li><strong>System settings</strong> &mdash; Admin only</li>
      </ul>

      <div class="help-tip">
        <i class="bi bi-lightbulb"></i>
        <div>Your current role is shown at the bottom of the sidebar under your name. The features visible in your navigation menu are filtered based on your role.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ==================== DASHBOARD ==================== -->
    <div class="help-topic" id="topic-dashboard">
      <h2><i class="bi bi-grid-1x2"></i> Dashboard</h2>
      <p class="topic-desc">The dashboard is your home screen. It shows a snapshot of today's activity, tailored to your role.</p>

      <% if (isAdmin || isManager) { %>
      <h3>Admin & Manager Dashboard</h3>
      <span class="help-role-badge admin">ADMIN</span> <span class="help-role-badge manager">MANAGER</span>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Task Statistics</strong> &mdash; Total tasks, pending, in progress, and completed counts for the team</li>
        <li><strong>Reward Summary</strong> &mdash; Total earned, pending amount, and paid amount across all users</li>
        <li><strong>Attendance Overview</strong> &mdash; Total users, logged in today, on leave, on weekly off</li>
        <li><strong>Per-User Metrics</strong> &mdash; Task completion rates and reward tracking for each team member</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="help-tip">
        <i class="bi bi-lightbulb"></i>
        <div>Click on any statistic card on the dashboard to navigate directly to the detailed view for that metric.</div>
      </div>
      <% } %>

      <h3>User Dashboard</h3>
      <span class="help-role-badge user">LOCAL_USER</span>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Total Tasks</strong> &mdash; Total number of tasks assigned to you (links to My Tasks)</li>
        <li><strong>Today's Tasks</strong> &mdash; Your tasks for the current date (recurring + one-time)</li>
        <li><strong>Personal Statistics</strong> &mdash; Tasks active, completed, and reward summary</li>
        <li><strong>Date Navigation</strong> &mdash; Browse tasks for different dates using Prev/Next buttons or date picker</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="help-tip">
        <i class="bi bi-lightbulb"></i>
        <div>When viewing a past date, incomplete tasks show as <strong style="color:#ef4444;">"Not Done"</strong> (in red) instead of "Pending" &mdash; making it easy to distinguish between missed work and today's pending tasks.</div>
      </div>

      <h3>Navigating the Dashboard</h3>
      <div class="help-step">
        <div class="help-step-num">1</div>
        <div class="help-step-content">
          <strong>Click "Dashboard" in the sidebar</strong>
          <p>This is the first item in the navigation menu and also the default landing page after login.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="help-step">
        <div class="help-step-num">2</div>
        <div class="help-step-content">
          <strong>Review your statistics cards</strong>
          <p>The top section shows summary cards with key numbers. Each card is clickable and leads to a more detailed view.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="help-step">
        <div class="help-step-num">3</div>
        <div class="help-step-content">
          <strong>Use date navigation (if available)</strong>
          <p>On the user dashboard, use the left/right arrows or date picker to view tasks for other days.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ==================== TASK OVERVIEW ==================== -->
    <div class="help-topic" id="topic-tasks-overview">
      <h2><i class="bi bi-check2-square"></i> Task Overview</h2>
      <p class="topic-desc">Tasks are the core of TaskFlow. There are two main types: one-time (adhoc) tasks and recurring tasks that repeat on a schedule.</p>

      <h3>Task Types</h3>
      <h4>One-Time (Adhoc) Tasks</h4>
      <p>A single task that needs to be done once. It has a due date and moves through statuses: <strong>Pending</strong> &rarr; <strong>In Progress</strong> &rarr; <strong>Completed</strong>.</p>

      <h4>Recurring Tasks</h4>
      <p>Tasks that repeat on a schedule. Each day's instance is tracked separately. Patterns include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Daily</strong> &mdash; Repeats every working day</li>
        <li><strong>Weekly</strong> &mdash; Repeats on specific days of the week (e.g., Monday, Wednesday, Friday)</li>
        <li><strong>Monthly</strong> &mdash; Repeats on a specific day of each month</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can start a session, complete it, and even log completions for past dates if you missed one.</p>

      <h3>Task Statuses</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong style="color:#f59e0b;">Pending</strong> &mdash; Task is created but work has not yet started</li>
        <li><strong style="color:var(--tf-accent);">In Progress</strong> &mdash; A work session has been started on the task</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#10b981;">Completed</strong> &mdash; Task is finished. Reward (if any) is automatically created</li>
        <li><strong style="color:#9ca3af;">Deactivated</strong> &mdash; Task has been disabled by an admin or manager</li>
      </ul>

