    <!-- ==================== SYSTEM CHAT ==================== -->
    <div class="help-topic" id="topic-system-chat">
      <h2><i class="bi bi-robot"></i> System Chat</h2>
      <p class="topic-desc">System Chat is an automated notification channel that keeps you informed about important events. You cannot reply to system messages.</p>
      <span class="help-role-badge all">ALL USERS</span>

      <h3>What is System Chat?</h3>
      <p>System Chat is a special read-only conversation that appears in your chat list. It is managed by TaskFlow automatically and delivers notifications about tasks, attendance, streaks, and other system events. You cannot send messages in this conversation.</p>

      <h3>Types of System Notifications</h3>

      <h4>Welcome Greeting</h4>
      <p>When your account is first created, you receive a welcome message in System Chat explaining the basics of TaskFlow and your role.</p>

      <h4>Task Notifications</h4>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Task Assigned</strong> &mdash; When a new task is assigned to you, you receive a notification with the task title and details</li>
        <li><strong>Deadline Approaching</strong> &mdash; A reminder is sent when a task's deadline is approaching</li>
        <li><strong>Overdue Task</strong> &mdash; If a task passes its due date without completion, you are notified</li>
        <li><strong>Task Deactivated</strong> &mdash; When a task assigned to you is deactivated by an admin or manager</li>
        <li><strong>Fallback Assignment</strong> &mdash; When a task falls to you as a backup assignee because the primary person is on leave</li>
      </ul>

      <h4>Daily Summary</h4>
      <p>Each day, you receive a summary of your tasks for the day: how many are pending, in progress, and completed. This helps you plan your workday.</p>

      <h4>Weekly Digest</h4>
      <p>At the start of each week, you receive a digest summarizing the previous week: total tasks completed, rewards earned, attendance summary, and any overdue items.</p>

      <h4>Streak Notifications</h4>
      <p>A <strong>streak</strong> means a continuous run of days where you completed all your assigned tasks without missing any. The longer you go without missing a day, the higher your streak.</p>
      <p><strong>How it works:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>When you complete your <strong>last remaining task</strong> for the day, the system checks how many previous consecutive days you also completed everything.</li>
        <li>If it is your first perfect day (no streak yet), you get: <em>"All tasks done for today! Great job — you've completed all 8 tasks."</em></li>
        <li>If you have <strong>3 or more consecutive days</strong>, you get a streak notification: <em>"5-day streak! You've completed all tasks on time for 5 consecutive days."</em></li>
        <li>If you <strong>miss even one task</strong> on any day, your streak resets to zero and starts fresh from the next perfect day.</li>
      </ul>
      <p><strong>Example:</strong></p>
      <ul>
        <li>Monday: All 8 tasks done — Day 1</li>
        <li>Tuesday: All 6 tasks done — Day 2</li>
        <li>Wednesday: All 7 tasks done — Day 3 — <strong>3-day streak!</strong></li>
        <li>Thursday: All 5 tasks done — Day 4 — <strong>4-day streak!</strong></li>
        <li>Friday: Missed 1 task — <strong>Streak broken</strong>, resets to 0</li>
        <li>Next Monday: All tasks done — Day 1 again (starts fresh)</li>
      </ul>
      <div class="help-tip">
        <i class="bi bi-lightbulb"></i>
        <div>Try to complete all your tasks every day to build a long streak. It is a great way to track your consistency and stay motivated.</div>
      </div>

      <h4>Task Reminders</h4>
