    <!-- ==================== MY ATTENDANCE ==================== -->
    <div class="help-topic" id="topic-my-attendance">
      <h2><i class="bi bi-calendar-check"></i> My Attendance</h2>
      <p class="topic-desc">View your login history, today's sessions, and monthly attendance calendar. Attendance is tracked automatically when you log in and out of TaskFlow.</p>
      <span class="help-role-badge all">ALL LOCAL USERS</span>

      <h3>How Attendance Works</h3>
      <p>Each time you log in to TaskFlow, a session is recorded with your login time. When you log out (manually or via auto-logout), the logout time is recorded. This creates a complete record of your working sessions for each day.</p>

      <h3>Multi-Session Attendance</h3>
      <p>TaskFlow supports multiple login/logout sessions per day. If you log in, log out for a break, and log in again, each session is tracked separately. The system calculates:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Total active time</strong> &mdash; Sum of all session durations for the day</li>
        <li><strong>Gap time</strong> &mdash; Time between sessions (break time)</li>
        <li><strong>First login</strong> &mdash; Your earliest login time of the day</li>
        <li><strong>Last logout</strong> &mdash; Your latest logout time of the day</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Today's Sessions</h3>
      <div class="help-step">
        <div class="help-step-num">1</div>
        <div class="help-step-content">
          <strong>Navigate to "My Attendance" in the sidebar</strong>
          <p>This opens your personal attendance page.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="help-step">
        <div class="help-step-num">2</div>
        <div class="help-step-content">
          <strong>View today's sessions at the top</strong>
          <p>The top section shows your current session status, login time, and any previous sessions for today with their durations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3>Attendance Calendar</h3>
      <p>Below today's sessions, a calendar view shows your monthly attendance at a glance:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Green</strong> &mdash; Present (logged in and worked)</li>
        <li><strong>Red</strong> &mdash; Absent (no login recorded)</li>
        <li><strong>Blue</strong> &mdash; On leave (approved leave)</li>
        <li><strong>Gray</strong> &mdash; Weekly off day</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Click on any date in the calendar to see the detailed session log for that day.</p>

      <h3>Monthly Summary</h3>
      <p>Below the calendar, a summary shows:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Days Present</strong> &mdash; Number of unique days you logged in during the month</li>
        <li><strong>Days Absent</strong> &mdash; Working days (excluding weekly offs and approved leaves) where no login was recorded</li>
        <li><strong>Attendance Rate</strong> &mdash; Percentage of expected working days you were present (capped at 100%). Logging in on a weekly off or leave day still counts as present but doesn't inflate the rate beyond 100%</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Login / Logout History</h3>
      <p>A detailed table below the calendar lists every login and logout event, including timestamps, session duration, and the reason for logout (if applicable).</p>

      <h3>Late Login Reason</h3>
      <p>If you log in after your scheduled shift start time, a modal will appear asking you to provide a reason for the late login. Select from the list of common reasons or type a custom explanation. This reason is recorded alongside your attendance entry and is visible to admins and managers.</p>

      <div class="help-tip">
        <i class="bi bi-lightbulb"></i>
        <div>Your attendance record is used by the system to determine fallback task assignments. If you are marked as on leave, your tasks may automatically fall to your designated backup assignee.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- ==================== ATTENDANCE DASHBOARD ==================== -->
